m1 <- lm(I(log(Total)) ~ I(NatIonalIty), data = f1617Totaless)
m2 <- update(m1, ~ . + NatIonalIty)
m3 <- update(m2, ~ . + CIty)
m4 <- update(m3, ~ . + UnIversIty)
m5 <- update(m4, ~ . + Female)
m6 <- update(m5, ~ . + Male)
m7 <- update(m6, ~ . + Type)

mtable(m1, m2, m3, m4, m5, m6, m7)

Reflection

In this study an analysis was carried out on the variation of foreign student number over time in Turkey. A relation between the total number of foreign students and time was successfully found. Furthermore, the countries where they mainly come from, the cities in Turkey they go to and, consequently, the universities that they mainly/are likely to join. 1. cleaning the data was a very time intensive task - took over 50% of the entire project time. 2. Choosing the right graph types and functions for data display was no easy feat. 3. The fact that new universities are founded over time made the analysis more difficult as it required creating of new datasets
